 the ancient city of Astorga in León, named in Latin <i>Asturica</i>. Compare   Ostorga  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Estorga","meanings":["Hispanic: altered form of Spanish   Astorga  ."]},{"name":"Ostorga","meanings":["Hispanic (mainly El Salvador): altered form of Spanish   Astorga  ."]}]},{"name":"e","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 鄂, a short form of present-day Hubei province: (i) from E (鄂), the name of an ancient state (located in Henan province), destroyed by the king Zhou, last king of the Shang dynasty (1600–1046  BC ). (ii) from the placename E (鄂), the name of a fief (located in Shanxi province) in the state of Jin during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ). (iii) from the placename E (鄂), the name of a fief (located in Hubei province) granted to the royal members of the state of Chu during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ). (iv) possibly a surname from minority ethnic groups in southwestern China. (v) said to be adopted as a new surname by Yue Ting, who changed his original name Yue (嶽) to E (鄂), because he fled to Huangmei in present-day Hubei province (called E (鄂) at that time) to avoid persecution after his father Yue Fei (1103–1142  AD ), a famous Chinese general in the Southern Song dynasty (1127 – 1279  AD ), was put to death by the then emperor."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Ramiro","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Visigothic: probably composed of <i>ragin</i> ‘advice’ + <i>māri</i>, <i>mēri</i> ‘famous’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Conde Ramiro Froilaz, de Astorga e Valdeorras was born about 1195, in Cifuentes, Guadalajara, Castilla-La Mancha, Spain, his father, Conde Fruela Díaz de Cifuentes, was 27 and his mother, Estefania Sanchez de Navarra, was 22. He died in 1170."},"et":{"aproximadamente 1195–1170":"umbes 1195–1170","11